title: Wall Street Breakfast April 26: Twitter Agrees to $44 Billion Musk Buyout
author: Seeking Alpha
dc:creator: Seeking Alpha
description: Twitter and its board on Monday came to a sale agreement with Elon Musk for $44 billion. Cenntro Electric Group shares are short circuiting after CEO Peter Wang began speaking and highlighting supply chain risks. Match Group rose after traders circulated a report that speculated the Tinder owner could be a possible target for Meta Platforms. Catch the WSB article here.
